# Project Structure

This is a shadcn/ui + Storybook design system (Vite + React + TS + Tailwind v4). Keep the structure intact.

## Where things live

- `src/components/ui/` - all shadcn components AND their colocated `*.stories.tsx`
- `src/lib/utils.ts` - the `cn()` helper; always use it for class merging
- `src/hooks/` - shared hooks
- `src/index.css` - the ONLY place for theme tokens (colors, radius, fonts)
- `.storybook/` - Storybook config (do not move or rename)
- `.github/workflows/` - CI (Chromatic)

## Hard rules

- Never relocate or rename `src/components/ui/`.
- Import via the `@/` alias (e.g. `@/components/ui/button`), never long relative paths like `../../components/ui/button`.
- Package manager is **npm** (a `package-lock.json` exists). Do not introduce pnpm or yarn.
- Aliases are defined in `components.json`: `ui -> @/components/ui`, `utils -> @/lib/utils`, `hooks -> @/hooks`, `lib -> @/lib`.

## Before committing

Run both and ensure they pass:

```bash
npm run build
npm run build-storybook
```
